You turn the pages of the tome to the fighters guild. It is embossed with the 
impression of a grand tower shield. The shield has the scenes of glorious 
conquest by kings of legendary status wearing ancient armor and wielding
powerful weapons that only a fighter could wield. This glorious guild was made
in the image of these once great kings, we can wield almost anything that one
would consider a weapon, and wear any armour that would protect one in battle.
The only requirement to join the guild is that you be experienced in the ways
of Darkwind, of at least 5th level, and possess strength befit of a warrior.
As any fighter would tell you, the best quality of a true fighter is that in
time of need, a fighter is never alone, there is a camaraderie among this
guild of warriors. Through extensive training and much experience, one learns
skills useful only to a true fighter, skills that are used mostly in combat!
A fighter's standing in the guild is earned in battle. Every worthy kill
grants Fighter experience, and your guild level rises on its own as that
experience accumulates - no coin, no study, only combat. Read 'fhelp
advancement' for the details.
For further assistance, ask any fighter to help you. The guild is located in
a keep just outside the City of Darkwind.

From COT, go: six north, exit, four east, south, southeast, enter.
